gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 112, Wizards 108
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns overcame a 16-point deficit from late in the second quarter, outscored Washington 31-19 in the fourth quarter, and defeated the Wizards, 112-108. Kevin Durant (28 points, five rebounds, five assists) and Devin Booker (27 points, eight assists) led Phoenix as they received 35 points from their non-starters. Daniel Gafford led Washington with a career-high 26 points along with 17 rebounds while Tyus Jones added 22 points and 11 assists. Phoenix snaps a 2-game skid and improves to 14-12 as the Wizards fall to 4-21.
